Today, I got up very early to make my first flight home. I slept on the first plane. I wrote in the San Francisco airport while waiting. I read a UX book on my second flight to Seattle. In Seattle, I waited for Cameron's plane to land, and then waited for her luggage. We took the link train back to the U District and then a Lyft back home. Shortly after that, I walked over to Safeway and picked up some ingredients for dinner. I made a new oven egg dish sort of like quiche. Cameron and I watched Seinfeld and went to bed. Today was a fine day. It was tiring because of the lack of sleep and the plane rides, but it wasn't bad. I'm happy to be back in Seattle! Today was a pretty good day. Nothing out of the ordinary, but I was happy at work. I like my coworkers and I am optimistic for my new work schedule.

Today, I got up at around 8:30 and went to Starbucks. I got my free coffee with the promotional tumblr I purchased in December. I sat and I read my UX book and worked on other things on my to do list. Cameron arrived around noon. She was in a sore mood because she "felt like a failure" due to not having accomplished certain goals, e.g. talking to housemates more or landing a publishing deal. I did my best to cheer her up, but became cross when I perceived her to start bickering with me. We played Magic The Gathering. We went to Goodwill, then Trader Joe's, then the library, and then home. We played video games together - Cameron played Pokemon, and I played Resident Evil. Cameron then had another bout existential malaise. She cheered up after watching some silly videos. I went for a long walk and updated my journal and completed my step count goals. We then did SA and went to bed. Today was a good day, but I have to admit to getting frustrated with Cameron's mood swings. I know she feels bad about them.

Cameron and I went to Costa's for breakfast. I had a breakfast burrito, which was very filling. Then we went to Slate coffee, and played games and did some separate work time. Later, I took a trip downtown and went to Ike's Pot Shop, where I picked up an inexpensive vape and a marijuana cartridge for it. After that, I went for a long walk and relaxed with Cameron. We stayed up late and watched Bruce Almighty. Today was a pretty solid day. A little frustration in the morning (a coffeless boy was getting impatient with how long it takes Cameron to get up and ready...) but that was really the only issue.

Cameron and I had a tense interaction to start the morning. Both of us have been getting generally irritated with each other, especially me with her in the morning. I went for a walk by myself, and we talked about it. I pushed for having morning alone time, since we've been spending so much uninterrupted time with each other. I really do think this is for the best; Cameron sleeps in and takes her time to get ready in the morning, while I can get up and go and be productive. It should work out. We went to Bean and Bagel and got breakfast, then parted ways. I worked on projects in starbucks, like UX stuff and writing, and she did hobbies at home. When I got back to the house, both of us were in much better moods. We played games, went for a walk, made pizza, watched Seinfeld, and had a good time. We did attempt SA, but it didn't work out. Raincheck. After this, Cameron played Stardew Valley and I figured out how to actually use the vape I purchased yesterday, and got nicely stoned. Today was a pretty good day. The morning conversation was tense but necessary. I feel better now that we made the plan we did. Tomorrow, I will get up and go to Starbucks alone. Cameron will meet up with me when she is ready - and then we will go downtown!

Woke up early and went to starbucks to have some personal time. I didn't accomplish much that was fun, but I did put a dent in some things on my to-do list. Cameron met up with me afterwards. We caught a bus to the link, and then took the link downtown. We got salt bagels at Pike Place Market, stopped by Target, and then went to Anchorhead Cafe. We played games and worked on separate projects there. Eventually we left and went home to have dinner. I made falafal for the first time using a Trader Joe's mix, and played resident evil. Then Cameron and I hung out in the room for the rest of the evening, save for when I went for a brief walk. Today was a solid day. It was nice being downtown - I really have to remember that. I felt a little sad at the end of the day for unknown reasons, but it was pretty light. I also download Rogue Legacy at full price, which hopefully was a good decision.

Today, I slept in with Cameron and then we parted ways. She went to a work event of some sort; I caught a bus to Kirkland. I arrived in Kirkland at about 2:30. I hung out and talked to family, and played smash bros with Peter. I left after dinner. I stopped at Safeway on the way home, went upstairs and talked to the housemates with Cameron, and prepared for work the next day before bed. That night, I had a pretty hard time sleeping. On the whole, a good day.

Today I got up very early to put stickers around the UW campus. Then I worked on UX stuff at starbucks before going to work early, where I cleaned out some drawers. I worked with a student I will refer to as Mr. Hudson today for the first time. It was fairly uneventful. After lunch I worked with my old student, who I will refer to as Treaty. Treaty's mood was a bit all over the place--he cried and laughed, was mellow and had bursts of energy. After work I wrote a quick parent email and did some grocery shopping. Then I rushed home to drop off my bags so I could go downtown to a UX event I wanted to attend. Cameron was in a dour mood when I arrived, and refused to talk about her day. I bused to the link and caught the link downtown. I accidentally attended the wrong lecture, but still gained some useful information. At home, I prepared for work and watched Cameron play a new video game. Today wasn't bad. Messing up the lecture I was supposed to attend wasn't that frustrating--it was actually sort of funny--but I am a little bummed I missed my UX event. Work was decent, though I was very tired all day because I slept poorly and got up extra early.

I had a hard time getting going in Starbucks this morning. My coffee didn't seem to be very effective. I feel like there's something psychologically disarming about drinking coffee NOT from the paper cup - as in, the caffeine just doesn't work as well, nor does it taste as good. I went to work. Details from work not included. At home, Cameron was feeling down. I made dinner, and tried to cheer her up. We watched Community together and then had SA. It was all super good! I had to pace to get my 10000 steps before going to bed.

Today, I tried to get work done at Starbucks but did not accomplish much. I went to work. Details from work are not included in this summary for privacy reasons. I stayed late to write session notes. I made pizza for me and Cameron and we watched It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia. Then as I was getting ready for bed, I made a bad joke about Cameron's organizational habits, which started a discussion.

Today, I slept in before work and did not go to Starbucks. I went to work. Details from work are not included for privacy reasons. I picked up Domino's after work. Cameron worked at Urban Luxe, I went for a walk. We watched TV and then played video games before going to bed.

Today, I got up and spent some time in Starbucks before going to work. Work was pretty good; I got to work with Mr. Hudson all day while supporting Treaty. There was a staff meeting, and then I finished up work with my data. At happy hour, I got to talk to Emily and Gina and later talked to Peter about the reasons he was leaving APL. I even smoked some pot outside if A Pizza Mart with coworkers. At home, Cameron and I hung out for a bit before she went off to a Velvet Q concert. I went for a walk up to a new Safeway while vaping. I played Rogue Legacy at home and then went to bed.

Today, I went to work in the morning. I tried to get as much stuff done there as possible. I picked up a flower for Cameron at the Saturday market. We hung out at the house for a while - I made lunch, Cameron played Sims. Then we went into Seattle to Cafe Ladro, where we played yugioh. Then we grabbed dinner at The Cheesecake Factory, which was really pleasant. We played video games at home while I was a bit high off the vape pen we bought.

Today, Cameron and I got and prepared to go to the Fremont Sunday Market. My mission there was to gift hunt; I successfully found a gift for my dad's birthday all the way in september, but no gift for either my mom or brother, whose birthdays are more immediate. We went to a new cafe after that - Milstead - and played yugioh. At home, I made enchiladas while Cameron cleaned out her extremely messy clothes situation, and when the food was done, we watched the first episode of Mob Psycho 100 season 2. Then I went for a walk, and when I returned, great SA.

Today, I got up and worked in Starbucks before going to work at 7:30. Work was typical and pleasant. After work, I went grocery shopping and went home to have leftover enchiladas with Cameron and watch Mob Psycho 100. Then I washed the ferrets' bedding and went to sleep.

Today, I got up and worked in Starbucks before going to work at 8:00am. Work was fine, but I was sleepy and have a bit of a cold so I felt out of it and go frustrated more easily. After work, I made stir fry at home and then went to Cafe Racer with Cameron, but I was ultimately too tired/sick feeling to stick around and I went home and went to bed.

Today, I worked in Starbucks and went to work. Work was a little frustrating, but nothing terrible. After work, I did a lot of errands: gift shopping, picking up items for Cameron, getting more toilet paper, and enchilada ingredients. This took about two hours, including an irritating moment in which I had to return some brownie mix for Cameron when our phones weren't communicating very well. I made the enchiladas at home, with just tofu this time. They turned out okay - the tofu I think needs to be flavored more before being put into the tortilla. Cameron and I ate and watched Seinfeld. Then Cameron started watching a show called You, and I went to bed.

Today, I worked in Starbucks and then went to work. Work was okay; I had a mild headache throughout it, and there were some frustrating moments, but it was doable. After work I made the decision to start doing my Session Notes (which I have been composing after work since I started at APL) in the morning, figuring I'll be more productive then. I had leftover enchiladas at home, and then Cameron and I went to Wayward Coffeehouse, where we played Yu-Gi-Oh (a game that has been frustrating me recently; it seems to me that Cameron's newer cards are a little unfair against my meat and potatoes deck). We did independent work after that, and I went home and went to bed earlier than Cameron. I still have an annoying cold. My headache lasted all day. I'm hoping I'll feel better over the weekend.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good. I stayed late until it was time to catch a bus to Redmond to meet up with Jordan at Dough Zone. We talked and caught up, and then went back to his house and watched Kingsmen: The Secret Service. Then he dropped me off at my parents' house in Kirkland.

Today, I slept in and then got a haircut. After my haircut, the rest of the afternoon was spent lounging around in Kirkland: doing independent work, celebrating my brother Peter's 25th birthday, talking to Peter and Luke. Pizza and cake for dinner. At around 8 in the evening, Luke and I took a bus back to Seattle and talked about UX and his future math teacher job. Then I walked home and met up with Cameron while our house was in the midst of a house show. I went to bed shortly after.
column8: Peter Joss, Luke Saling, Cameron Eldridge

column5: Today, Cameron and I slept in and then did some cleaning as we prepared for our day. We went to Poindexter cafe and then Slate Coffee Roasters. We did some chores and searched for Cameron's lost fake ID. Then we got dinner and played games at a joint called Mox in Ballard that lets you borrow and test out tabletop games. We had a great time! I'd very much like to return there. I feel like it could be a regular haunt for us.

Today, I slept in before meeting up with my friend Yusuke at a restaurant called Sultan. He'd just gotten in from a long flight from Japan, so he was very tired, and since he's been gone from America for two years, his English speaking ability has atrophied a bit. We caught up, and then I took him back to my house, where he'll be staying for the next couple weeks. Then he we took a quick outing to Pike Place Market and returned to the house. Yusuke went to a cafe to try to stay awake (to set his body clock to Seattle time), and I did various chores. Cameron, Yusuke and I played video games, and then Cameron and I played Star Realms: Frontiers, and then I went to bed. It's great having Yusuke around! I've missed the guy a lot.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine, aside from one tough moment with my kiddo. After work, I went home and ate dinner. Then I cleaned the room while waiting for Cameron to get home. When Cameron was home, we played Star Realms. Then I chatted with Yusuke for a second, and went to bed.

Today I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good. After work, I went shopping and hung out in my room at home. When Yusuke got home, I talked to him and played a bit of Smash Bros. Then I had a phone call with Cameron.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good. After work I had a FaceTime call with Cameron. Her interview in San Francisco went well. I don't want her to move away from Seattle, so this new bums me out. I went for a walk and updated my journal. Then I went to bed.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was calm, aside from one moment. I stayed late at work, in part to call for legal advice. I met up with Yusuke in Capitol Hill and got food/drinks with him at the Unicorn. We smoked a cigar at the house, and then walked to Citra on University Way. Then we got falafel, hung out at the house with housemates playing cards, and went to bed.

After making breakfast and picking up my coffee, I cleaned the room and listened to music. Cameron arrived back from San Francisco at around 4:00. We ate pizza and did SA. She went to see a movie with Aly, and I went to Citra. Cameron met up with me there afterwards.

I walked to Petco and got some supplies.Then Cameron and I got brunch at Wayward Vegan Cafe. We went to a vintage store in Fremont, and then hung out at the Fremont Coffeehouse. Chores at home. Mob Psycho 100 season 2. SA, then bed.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. After work, I did grocery shopping, and went home to eat dinner. Then I met up with Cameron at Cafe on the Ave. We played yu gi oh and talked. Then I met up with Yusuke at Citra and walked to Safeway and home with him. Turns out today was his last day in Seattle! Sad to have him go already.

Today, I said goodbye to Yusuke before working in Starbucks. I went to work. After work Cameron and I talked and cleaned the room for a bit. I had dinner. We looked at yu gi oh cards for a while. Then I went for a walk to get steps before going to bed.

Today, I got up and worked in Starbucks before going to work. After work, I picked up some baking ingredients for Cameron's birthday. I walked around searching for a couple packs of yu gi oh cards to throw into Cameron's present, which took a while and involved me walking down to Pink Gorilla on the Ave. Cameron came home from work at about 7:00. We talked and hung out. I played some rogue legacy and went to bed.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I met up with Cameron at Wayward Coffeehouse to deliver her computer charger; then I took the opportunity to do some last-minute stuff for her birthday. I went to Fremont and purchased a venus fly trap for her. At home, at made her magic cookie bars, and then covered up the evidence so it'd be a surprise.

Today, I got up early and set up a display of gifts for Cameron's birthday. I worked in Starbucks before work. Work was frustrating. After work, it was Cameron's birthday: lunch at Morsel, bus to Bellevue, walk around the mall, dinner at Maggiano's, bus back to the U District for an escape room, back home. The day wasn't as happy as I wanted, but there were still really fun moments - the escape room and dinner, notably. Once home, we drank before going to bed. Cameron was existential for periods throughout today, which I found frustrating.

Today, Cameron and I bused over to my parent's house to borrow the car. We drove it first to Bellevue to pick up something that Cameron forgot at Maggiano's and to get bagels n coffee, and then we took it to Snoqualmie pass. We walked along a snowy trail and enjoyed the sights. We got dinner at Twede's cafe in North Bend. Then we went back to Seattle and worked at a couple of coffee shops before returning to our house. We had a tense conversation before bed. I was bummed and irritated that, like Friday, today's part of Cameron's birthday weekend had not gone as well as I'd planned. In retrospect, I wish I'd controlled my grumpiness better at this point. I ought to be more understanding of the thoughts and feelings that drag Cameron's mood down, and not take them quite so personally.

Today, Cameron and I did some errands in the morning while we had use of a car. We took some clothes she wanted to get rid of to appropriate stores on the Ave to sell or donate them. Then we took the car to a big Goodwill in Ballard, but we didn't find much good there. It started to snow around this point. I took the car to Kirkland and spent the next few hours there for my mom's birthday celebration. We got dinner at a Pho place and ate cake at home. I bused back to Seattle. Cameron and I watched some TV before turning in.

Today, work was canceled because of the snow. Cameron and I tried to get bagels at Bean and Bagel, but the air was so cold and the buses weren't running that well, so we ended up eating at home. Then we bused/took a lyft to the Chocolati in Greenlake, where we worked all afternoon before returning home. At home, I walked to the nearest Domino's to pick up pizza, and then Cameron and I ate pizza and hung out in the room. Just before leaving Chocolati, Cameron got her offer letter for the job she applied to in San Francisco. She is likely going to take it. I was put in a sad/weird mood for the rest of the day after this, for all the obvious reasons. I didn't really want Cameron to leave, but it seems like we're going to be going long distance :(

Today there was another snow day, so again no work. Cameron and I got bagels at Bean and Bagel and picked up coffee before heading home. We watched a movie called Velvet Buzzsaw, and part of a Spiderman movie. Cameron went to hang out with her friend Aly, while I did chores at home. When she got back we talked and sat by each other, and then I went to bed in anticipation of actually having work tomorrow. I decided I felt better about the whole Cameron moving to San Francisco thing. It is helpful to look at it as an opportunity for personal growth and independent time apart from Cameron before reuniting a stronger couple. While she is gone, I can potentially spent time in Japan and make a lot of progress on my UX goals. I will miss her a lot, but I will also be able to reunite with her in San Francisco sooner than I think.

Today, I got up and worked in Starbucks. Work started late today because of the snow. Work was fine. After work, I had dinner and hung out in the room until Cameron got home from work. Then we watched more Spiderman: Homecoming.
Today, I got up and worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, Cameron and I kept watching Spiderman: Homecoming, and then it was time for bed.

Today, I got up and worked in starbucks before going to work. Work was fine - and we all got to leave before 2:00 because of another snow system moving in to Seattle. I braved the long lines at Safeway to get groceries for the snow-in, and then went home. SA. Cameron and I later watched Wreck It Ralph 2, and then went out to a gathering at Cameron's friend Aly's place. It was too much for me and I left early.
Today, Cameron and I lazed around in the house before eventually ending up at Cafe Racer. We played games at Racer - including a new game called Splendor - and had a nice time.

Today, Cameron and I got breakfast at Portage Bay, and then went to a cafe called Revolution. We stuck around there for a few hours, playing games and doing solitary computer work, and then we went for a walk through Greenlake Park. Then we ended up at Peet's Coffee, where be played yugioh. It started snowing pretty heavily around this time. We picked up some pizza at A Pizza Mart, and ate it at the house and drank cider. SA.

Today, I didn't have work due to the weather. Cameron and I hung out in the room. We got dinner/late lunch at Rain City Burgers, and then hung out at Broadcast Coffee. When Broadcast Coffee closed we moved to Wayward Coffeehouse.

Today, I didn't have work due to the weather. Cameron and I stayed in the room until going out of Broadcast Coffee. We played a game, and then Cameron met up with her friend Aly. I worked on writing. Then Cameron and I worked on how we would be moving her to San Francisco. Back in the room, we watched Seinfeld and SA.

Today, I had no work due to the weather. Cameron and I hung out in the room and discussed/argued about how we were going to move her to San Francisco. I went to Wayward Coffeehouse at around 2 and worked there until 5. Then I did some preparatory work for Valentine's Day before Cameron got home from work. Cameron painted me and I played Switch games. Then we played a round of Overcooked before I went to bed.

Today, I worked in starbucks before going to work. Work was a late start, and I left early for Valentine's Day plans. Cameron and I met up at Cedars, an Indian restaurant. We then went to the Pacific Science Center. We hung out in the Armory at Seattle Center, and then got pizze. I gave her my main valentine's present around this time. Then we saw a laser light show at the Pacific Science Center. At home, we did SA and watched part of a movie.

Today, I worked in starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I hung out at Urban Luxe Cafe. Then I went home and played with the ferrets and went to bed. Cameron was out with friends in Olympia.
Today, I wrote in Herkimer coffee in the morning. Then I hung out in the room and worked on various things. Cameron got home later that evening.

Today, Cameron and I went to the Fremont Sunday Market, and then got lunch at Stone Way Cafe. I later met up with my friend Jack and his friend Billy, who were visiting from Canada. We played games at Jack's house and caught up. I got home late.
column8: Jack Still, Billy Reeves, Cameron Eldridge

column5: Today, I helped Cameron pack to go to San Francisco. Cameron later went to get a check from work. I hung with her in the evening.
Today, I helped Cameron pack for San Francisco. She hung out with her friend Aly later, and I went to the dentist. Later in the evening, we went out to dinner and rode the Seattle Ferris Wheel.

Today, we packed, got the rental cat, loaded everything in, and began our drive down to San Francisco. We did not leave the house until past 5pm. We arrived at my aunt's house at around 9pm. We talked to Aunt Robby, SA, and went to bed.

Today, I got up early and talked to Aunt Robby. Cameron and I left on the longest part of our drive, Portland OR to Redding CA. The drive went by without a hitch, and we took Siskyou pass to get there. In Redding, we got Costco pizza, watched TV, took marijuana edibles, and went to bed.

Today, Cameron and I finished the last leg of our drive and arrived in San Francisco. We met up with her parents and moved stuff into the apartment. Cameron and I hung out,  SA, got dinner, and went to a unique museum called the Onedome.

Today, Cameron and I got breakfast and met up with her parents. We shopped at Ikea all day, got lunch, and then I was taken to the airport. My plane ride home was passed with a documentary about North Korea. I stopped at Ross and bought new shoes. That night, I stayed up late reorganizing my Seattle bedroom.
Today, I finished organizing my room, went shopping, and otherwise bummed around. It's sad and boring without Cameron here. I find myself really looking forward to joining her in San Francisco

Today, I got up and wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good! After work, I went grocery shopping, made dinner, and video called with Cameron. Then I learned a little HTML and video called with Cameron again.

Today, I got up and worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good again! After work I did some errands, like go to the post office and shop. At home, I failed to be productive because I a)was a little horny and ended up messaging Cameron, and b)got preoccupied with a poor purchase I made earlier that day. I vaped and went to bed upset.
Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I bought some ice cream and hung out in the room and dealt with returning a product I bought. Then I relaxed in bed.
Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good. After work, I came home and had dinner and hung out. Then I did a video call with Cameron and watched Survivor.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was normal. I left work early and did errands before going home in Kirkland. I had dinner with my family and then watched a movie with Jordan. Then I hung out with Peter for a bit before going to bed.

I hung out with Peter after he came home from work and listened to music. Peter and I went out to dinner and talked before I went home in Seattle. I set up an old TV in my bedroom and did a video call with Cameron before going to bed.
Today, I slept in and then went into work to complete a few projects. Then I did some shopping and returned to the house, where I did chores and relaxed, and eventually did a video call with Cameron.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine, Gina was out today. After work I went to the post office and delivered a letter to Cameron, and then went home and had dinner. I did a video call with Cameron because she missed me.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was wearisome, Gina was out again today. After work I went grocery shopping and had dinner at home. I was a little frustrated and unproductive, and I ended up giving Cameron a video call because...I missed her.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work I went home and had dinner and tried out a new strategy wherein I shower etc immediately so I'm almost nearly prepared for work the next day and can just lounge around in bed. I read and wrote. I ended up doing two video calls with Cameron, one to write with her, and two when she started feeling existential.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I mailed a quick letter to Cameron and went home. Cameron and I had our Survivor watching date tonight. We encountered a bit of conflict because of something I did, and we talked it out before going to bed.
Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was alright. After work, I went to Ike's and got some more pot. Then I smoked and did a quick FaceTime call with Cameron before going to bed.

Today I got up, set up the ferrets in my room, and left for my haircut at 11:30. After my haircut, I wrote in a Starbucks, and then went home to my parents. I had dinner, and hung out waiting for Peter to finished homework. Then we listened to music together.

Today, I got up and walked to Down Pour coffee. I worked on stuff at my computer and then played smash bros with Peter. Then my family did a 93rd birthday lunch for my grandfather at Iver's, a seafood restaurant. I went back to Seattle afterwards and did a video call with Cameron, watching monster factory and last week tonight.

Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was pretty good. After work, I did some errands and texted Cameron. I wasn't very productive at home, and when Cameron got home from work/cafe time, we FaceTimed.
Today I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work I did some shopping for Cameron at Daiso and then delivered gifts to her friend Aly. Then I read before going to bed.
Today I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good, despite a sort of stressful start in Starbucks researching Japan things! After work I read in bed for the rest of the day.
Today, I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was very good! After work I made dinner and watched Survivor with Cameron.
Today I worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was ok. After work I hung out in my room--smoked a little pot, played Resident Evil, went to bed.

Today I got up and wrote in Cowen Park Cafe. I ran into a student from work there. I did some shopping. I tried to get some other chores done but didn't succeed in being very productive.
Today, I wrote at home instead of Starbucks, and then I went to work. Work was a bit rough. After work, I did errands before going home.
Today, I wrote at home before going to work. Work was alright. After work, I edited a bit of audio from my journal and read before going to bed.
Today, I wrote at home before going to work. Work was another rough day. After work, I read Cameron's book, Lucid, at home, and then did a FaceTime call with her.

Today, I wrote at home before going to work. I woke up in a bit of sour mood, but work started off really good, and then ended frustratingly. I went to happy hour with coworkers because this week has been a rough one. Then I read Cameron's book Lucid and went to bed.

Today I wrote at home before going to work. Work was good, though I had to write a lot of session notes. After work I caught a bus to Kirkland and had dinner with my family. Then I watched "Sorry To Bother You" with Jordan.

Today, I updated my journal and walked to Down Pour Cafe to work on personal projects. Then I hung out with Peter and listened to music. After dinner with my family I caught a bus back to Seattle and watched Survivor with Cameron.
Today, I worked on things at Wayward Coffeehouse and then did shopping chores until meeting up with Tyler. Tyler and I had pizza and drinks at A Pizza Mart, and then moved to Flowers Bar.
Today I wrote in my room before going to work. Work was good. After work, I read my book in my room and did laundry.
Today I wrote in my room before going to work. Work was alright. After work, I worked on editing clips from my audio journal for Cameron.

Today I worked on the audio journal project in the morning before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I read in my room, and then did a video call with Cameron. I am feeling a little tired and sad; I think I need to get out of the room more on weekdays.
Today, I wrote in my room before going to work. Work was okay. After work, I worked on stuff in my room.

Today, I wrote in my room before going to work. Work was a bit of a drag. After work, I took the bus to Redmond and met up with Jordan at Dough Zone. We watched a movie at his place afterwards. Had an unexpected conversation.

Today, I went to Down Pour cafe in the morning and then hung out at home. I did my taxes with Peter, had dinner, and hung out and listened to music with him and played Smash Bros. Then I took a bus to Seattle and watched Survivor with Cameron.
Today, I slept in and then took a bus to downtown Seattle. I shopped around at Pike Place Market and worked at Coffee Works. I went grocery shopping and helped Cameron with some edits.
Today, I wrote in my room before going to work. Work was decent. After work, I wrote a letter at the library, made dinner, and read before bed.
Today, I wrote at Starbucks before going to work. Work was okay. After work, I got dinner with Aly, and then did a FaceTime call with Cameron.
Today, I read at home before going to work. Work was a bit challenging. I shopped around for Cameron after work and then did a FaceTime call with her later.
Today, I read in my room before going to work. Work was good. After work, I cleaned and packed for my trip to San Francisco.

Today, I packed in my room before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I did some last minute things at home before going and catching my plane to San Francisco. Cameron and I went to her place, SA, and got pizza and watched Monster Factory.
Today, Cameron and I went to Japantown, and spent the afternoon looking in shops, in a cafe, writing, and exploring.
Today, Cameron and I got brunch, explored the Palace of Fine Arts, and then went to an arcade and later out to dinner on the wharf.

Today, I got up and went to work with Cameron, and then spent some time reading/writing/researching in the cafe in the lobby of her office building. Cam and I ate lunch together and I went to a Starbucks until she was off work. Then we walked around the mall and got some pizza. Back in the room, we took a bath together but Cameron's mood grew depressed and we had a talk.
Today, I went to work with Cameron and hung out in various cafes until she was done. Afterwards, we went to the pier, got doughnuts, walked around, and eventually returned to her apartment.

Today, I stayed back in the apartment while Cameron went to work. I slept in and played video games and did a little cleaning. Then I walked downtown and got Peet's coffee. When Cameron was off work, we got dinner at The Cheesecake Factory and then saw the movie "Us."

Today, I got up and bused down to Cameron's office with her. I got coffee at Peet's and then walked around Chinatown. After work,  I was feeling really fed up with the idea of returning to work at APL. We went to Jane on Larkin, Goodwill, and then I got pizza and we hung out in Cam's room and watched Survivor.

Today, I slept in and later walked downtown to meet with Cameron on her lunch break. I then walked back to the apartment so I could lock the room, and then bused downtown and wrote in Peet's coffee. Cameron and I got drinks that night, and we talked about my writing; I got a little heated with some of her feedback and made the mood tense for a while.
Today, Cameron and I went to the exploratorium, an interactive science museum. We spent all afternoon there. Afterwards, we got pizza and watched Mob Psycho in the room.
Today, Cameron and I watched Mob Psycho before going to the airport and parting ways. The flight home was uneventful. I researched job opportunities in my bedroom until it was time to sleep.

Today, I worked on my resume in Starbucks before going to work. Work was tolerable. After work, I printed my resume and rushed downtown to apply in person for a job. Then I got dinner at Cafe On The Ave and did a Facetime call with Cameron.
Today, I wrote at home before going to work. Work was frustrating. After work, I went home, updated my journal, and did my laundry.
Today I wrote in Solstice Cafe before going to work. Work was okay. After work, I did a video call with Cameron and watched the remaining episodes of Mob Psycho 100 season 2.
Today, I wrote at home before going to work. Work was okay. After work, I bused to Kirkland and had dinner and hung out with my family.
Today, I got up early and drove to Mark Twain Elementary to visit. Visiting was a lot of fun! Afterwards, I had a dentist appointment. I hung out at home for the rest of the day.

column5: Today, I got coffee with my old coworker Allison. It was great fun catching up with her. Then, I went to downtown kirkland to have a haircut. Back at my parent's house, I had lunch with pop. I hung out for the rest of the afternoon and bused home to Seattle after dinner. I did a video call with Cameron and watched One Punch Man.

Today, I slept in and then went to Herkimer Coffee. I went grocery shopping and hung out in my room, where I began feeling depressed. I cleaned and prepared for work and updated my journal. I read and hung out before bed.
Today, I wrote in Wayward Coffeehouse before going to work. Work was decent. After work, I hung out at home and played minecraft and such.
Today I wrote in Peet's Coffee before going to work. Work was bumpy but okay. After work I tried to make a minecraft server and did a facetime call with Cameron.
Today, I wrote at Peet's coffee before going to work. Work was good. After work, I did a video call with Cameron. We walked and watched anime.
Today, I wrote in Peet's Coffee before going to work. Work was good. After work, I had dinner and ended up doing a video call with Cameron.

Today, I went to Herkimer for coffee and then wrote in my room. I met up with Tyler for drinks on the Ave. I went grocery shopping and tried to check chores off of my to-do list.

Today, I wrote in Peet's Coffee before going to work. Work was alright. After work, I went for a jog and made some pizza and did a video call with Cameron to cheer her up after her dwarf hamster's passing.
Today, I wrote in Peet's Coffee before going to work. Work was a bit stressful. After work, I ate a quick dinner and took my work to Cafe Racer, where I bought a drink and was productive.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was okay, better than yesterday. After work, I went for a jog , had dinner, and did a video call with Cameron.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was alright. After work, I lazed around and updated my journal.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good. After work, I met up with Peter at Delfino's pizza. We went back to Kirkland together. I met up with Jordan briefly, and then hung out with Peter some more.
Today, I helped my dad move couches around and wrote in Down Pour cafe. Then I hung out with Peter until dinner. I took a bus back to Seattle and watched Survivor with Cameron.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was tough. After work I went for a jog, made dinner, and took an evening to relax.
Today I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was normal. After work, I met up with Tyler and conducted the first phase of a UX portfolio project.
Today I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was interesting because of a field trip, but good. After work I went for a jog and did a video call with Cameron.
Today I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work I hung out in my room and later updated my journal.

Today I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work I met up with Tyler and we got food around the international district. He dropped me off in Kirkland where I spent the night. I watched a movie with Cameron before going to bed.

In the afternoon, I listened to music with Peter, went for walk, and worked on things from my to-do list.

I did my grocery shopping and then caught a bus to the big Third Place Books up north, where I wrote in a cafe until Jay Kristoff (author) started his talk. I then bused home and went to bed.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was decent. After work, I went for a jog, made pizza, and got a drink at Flowers bar. Then I took a quick bus trip to Ike's Pot Shop and picked up some weed before going home and going to bed.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was good. After work, I mailed a letter and hung out with Aly for a bit. Then, I tried working on writing at home, but quickly got frustrated and did a video call with Cameron.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I watched Survivor with Cameron.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I went for a jog, had dinner, and cleaned my room before watching Survivor with Cameron.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. I left work early to catch a bus up to Vancouver, where I met up with Jack and got food and drinks and played Kirby Air Ride.

Today, I got up, had breakfast, and went to catch my bus back to Seattle. When I got back to Seattle, I grabbed dinner in Uwajimaya. I took my stuff back home and then went back to the International District to buy a pet crate from someone on Craigslist. Later, I unpacked and prepared for the work week.
Today, I got up and worked in Starbucks before going to work. Work was normal. After work, I did some errands and chores and then did a video call with Cameron until it was time to go to bed.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was okay, but I was a little agitated. I did some errands and chores after work, and then went to see Nausicaa of the Valley of the Wind in theaters.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was okay. After work, I spent a while cleaning and organizing my bedroom.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was a bit rough. After work, I did some grocery shopping and cooking for Cameron's visit.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I went home to care for the ferrets, then took a bus to Kirkland. I had dinner with my family and hung out with Peter. Then I picked up Cameron from the airport.

Today, I got breakfast at Portage Bay Cafe with Cameron. We spent time at Elliot Bay Cafe in the Capitol Hill bookstore before seeing the movie Detective Pikachu. Then, we got dinner at the Cheesecake Factory and hung out at Gameworks bar.

Today, Cameron and I hung out at the Folklife Festival in Seattle Center. We spent all afternoon there. Later, we had dinner at home and watched Princess Mononoke.

Work was rough because I was so tired. After work, I cleaned my room and organized things before getting in to bed and going to sleep early.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was decent. I stayed late at work to catch up on things. After work, I hung out in my room and then went for a walk.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I stayed late to catch up on extra work, and then caught a bus to Kirkland. I spent the night there and did chores for my family because they're gone and in Oregon for the weekend.

Today I got up, fed the cats, and went to a dentist appointment. Then, I drove to Seattle and went to work. Work was fine. After work, I organized and prepared to move stuff to my parent's house in Kirkland, and then hauled stuff to the car and drove it over. I smoked and went to bed at my parent's house.

Today, I got up and drove to a couple cafes. The battery in the car died at the second cafe I went to, stranding me in a parking lot for the next few hours. Eventually I got the car jumpstarted with the help of my Aunt Jean. I went to the post office and then my parent's house to do some things on my to-do list. Then, I went to my haircut. After my haircut I returned to the house briefly, then caught buses back to Seattle, where I did a video call with Cameron in which we sorted through part of her belongings. I took a long walk afterwards before goign to bed.

column5: Today, slept in and then walked to Chocolati Cafe in Greenlake. I spent a couple hours there, and then walked to the Chocolati in Wallingford. I took a bus home and had dinner. Then I organized things in my room.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was decent. After work, I had dinner, tidied my bedroom, and did a video call with Cameron to sort her belongings

I got dinner and she helped me with a UX project. I walked home, then walked back to Third Place Book because I forgot to take a picture of the cafe, and then I walked back home and got ready for bed.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. After work, I organized things in the room with Cameron.
Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was fine. After work, I went to Citra and got frozen yogurt, stopped by goodwill, and then worked on moving chores at my house.

Today, I wrote in Starbucks before going to work. Work was decent, though I got very tired in the afternoon. After work, I caught a bus to Kirkland and had dinner with my family. Then I listened to music with Peter. Later, I took the Subaru to Seattle and went to bed.

Today, I worked on writing a letter to Cameron in bed before taking the ferrets to a vet appointment in Kirkland. After the appointment I ate lunch at home and took the van back to Seattle to pack up more of my stuff. I worked on that until near six-thirty, drove home, had dinner with my family, and then rushed to downtown Kirkland to meet with my friend Tyler to work on my UX project and get drinks. I did a video call with Cameron before going to bed.

Today I worked on organizing my belongings and other miscellaneous chores before having the usual small birthday celebration with my family plus Luke and Pop. I worked on more organization tasks before catching a bus home to Seattle.
Today I worked on things in Starbucks before going to work. Work was decent. After work, I made a trip to Petco, and then organized things in my room with Cameron's help over a video call.
Today, I organized in my room instead of going to Starbucks, before going to work. Work was fine. After work I tried organizing my room more.

Today, I cleaned things in the room before going to work. Work was hot and long. After work, I did some errands but had bad luck, did a video call with Cameron, and had dinner with Jack while he was in town.
Today I organized my room before going to work. Work was fine. After and during work I did more errands, bused home to Kirkland, and had more things taken from my Seattle room back to Kirkland.

Today, I organized my room before going to work. Work was bittersweet. I said goodbye to my coworkers and met up with Cameron. Cam and I went to her philosophy graduation. I went home and had dinner and cleaned more while Cameron saw a friend and later went to a party.

Today, I got up early and dismantled the ferret cage. Then I went and picked up the rental car. My parents helped take some last things from my room, and helped me clean. I attended Cameron's undergraduate graduation. We finished packing afterwards, which took longer than expected. Then we drove to my Aunt Robby's house in Portland, arriving around midnight.

Today, Cameron and I got up, hung out with Aunt Robby for a bit, and then started on the big drive to San Francisco. We completed the drive by close to 9pm. We encountered traffic and I had my first accident, a fender bender. At Cameron's apartment, we hastily unpacked so I could return the rental car.

column5: Today, I slept in and Cameron went to work. I got food and coffee at Jane on Larkin, and then assembled the ferret cage. Then, I spent the rest of the afternoon cleaning and unpacking and organizing. When Cameron was home, we had a few small disputes, and then hung out with Cameron's friend Aly and Aly's friend Sophia, drinking and playing clue.

column5: Today, I made got up with Cameron and eventually went downtown to write in a cafe. I did errands and, later, when Cam was off work, went to a place called Quetzal Internet Cafe. Later, we had an interrupted SA attempt followed by me attempting to express concern about her weight gain.

Today, I woke up to find Cameron angry at me because of what I'd said the night before. After she left for work I began to feel discouraged with our relationship; we spoke briefly during her lunch break, in which I angrily spoke of her bad habits. I stewed in a Peet's Coffee until she was off work. Afterwards, there was tense discussion and the idea of breaking up, which I thought on and rejected. The rest of the evening was spent relaxing with video games.

Today, I woke up with Cameron. I went out writing downtown, and then did some cleaning and other errands. When Cameron was home from work, I started feeling a tightness in my chest, which lead to another discussion about our relationship.

Today, I woke up with Cameron. I tried to do writing at a cafe called Equator Coffee, but only ruminated on what I thought could be an ending relationship with Cameron. I felt scared and walked around, eventually ending up back at the apartment, where I sat on the bed and played video games and googled things. When Cameron was home, we went out and got drinks.

Today, Cameron and I got breakfast, and then went out to the Legion of Honor, and then a nearby beach. We hung out, talked, and read on the beach. There was some discussion about our relationship, in which we agreed passion had always been a bit of a struggle. Later, we were in the room, both feeling restless and uncertain.

Today, Cameron and I went to the Castro District, where we walked around and hung out in a cafe. Later, we were back in the room, where Cam took a LSAT practice test and I worked on various personal projects and went grocery shopping.

Today, I went to a cafe and later hung out in the room while Cameron was at work. I continued to debate my relationship with Cameron. When she got home, things were tense, and Cameron ended the relationship. I didn't fight it, and we talked about it, eventually watching A Castle In The Sky.

Today, I struggled with the fact that Cameron and I had broken up. I regretted it and attempted to get back together with her once she was off work, but we talked about it again and decided it was best. We got dinner at the Cheesecake Factory and saw the movie Booksmart later.
Today, I spent the morning moping around and reading relationship articles online. After Cameron was off work, we watched big brother in the room together.
Today, I wrote in a starbucks in downtown San Francisco, meeting up with Cameron for lunch once. Later, Cameron and I went to a bookstore-cafe and hung out. We got pizza after.
Today, I worked on a project for Cameron in the apartment, and then later met up with Cameron to drink ciders and go shopping. Afterwards, we got mexican food and hung out in the apartment.
Today, Cameron and I went to a flea market on treasure island, and later to the San Francisco museum of modern art to see a Warhol exhibit.
Today, Cameron and I went to the Pride parade and later hung out in the apartment and worked on separate projects. We then watched Porco Rosso and went to bed.
Today, I updated my journal and worked on various projects in the apartment while Cameron was at work. After Cameron was off work, we went to a kickboxing class together.

Today, I went out to the Legion Of Honor and De Young museums, and later finished up an anniversary gift for Cameron. After Cameron was off work  we went shopping and then got dinner at the Cheesecake factory.
Today, I wrote in the apartment while Cameron was at work. I got Philz coffee. After work Cameron and I went to a cafe, sat in a park, and then saw the new Spiderman movie.

Today, Cameron and I hung around in the apartment before going to a museum called the Academy of Science. We then tried to go to a particular cafe but it was closed, so we went to Ghirardelli Square instead and got chocolate and watched fireworks.

Today, I organized, cleaned, packed my belongings, and did some last errands for Cameron. I met up with her at the train station and said goodbye. I caught a flight to Portland and made my way to Aunt Robby's house, where I went to bed.

Today, I got up and talked to aunt robby and then worked on writing all day; however, all throughout the day I suffered from a sense of growing loneliness and unease, which culminated with me going to bed feeling sad.
Today, I got up and talked to aunt robby and then attempted to work on my writing for most of the day. Other than a brief walk, this was my entire day, and I made little writing progress.

Today, I wrote in the house and later bused up to downtown Portland; there, I did clothes shopping and ended up at a cafe in Powell's bookstore; later, I pontificated in Pioneer Square and began feeling optimistic about things. I spent the evening sitting around at my Aunt's house.

Today, I wrote at the house before going back to downtown Portland. I walked across the Burnside bridge and ended up at a small cafe. I walked around a bit more, got an egg sandwich, and returned to Lake Oswego. Later, Aunt Robby and I went to trivia night at a nearby bar.

column5: Today, I spent the day sitting and writing at my aunt's house, other than a short excursion to get lunch with my cousin Lisa. I had an intensifying feeling of guilt all throughout the day.

column5: Today, I hung around Aunt Robby's house and wrote, aside from spending some time writing at a nearby starbucks.

Today I threw up the water I had in the morning before going and getting blood drawn. My results came in later, and even later came a message from Dr. Yang. My sodium levels are very low and she wants to test me for something called "Addison's Disease." Already a very stressful day, this brought my anxiety to a new high.

I threw up my dinner just as I started it, but I stubbornly managed to return after that and keep eating. That night, I had nightmares of ending the world.

Today, after hours of nausea and discomfort and anxiety, I finally got myself to go to the doctor and take the recommended tests for Addison's disease. I was ok for this, and webt back home, where I tried to eat. After a couple hours my doctor called me and told me to go to the emergency room because my sodium had gotten lower. I spent the night in the hospital.

Today I spent my first whole day in the hospital. I was nauseous in the morning and threw up a little bit, barely eating my breakfast, even with nausea medicine. At noon my appetite came back. I was given a cortisol pill. I spoke with different doctors often and had to be supervised to get out of bed. My blood was drawn and my vitals were taken frequently. Slowly I began to feel better.

Today I mostly just layed around in bed, but I found I was feeling significantly better; I was given an iPad by my nurse and I went for walks. In the evening I did a video call with Cameron, and after that I sat by a big window in a sitting room down the hall, where I reflected on my relationship with Cameron. I had a cute nurse named Cathy that evening.

In the afternoon, I ended up chatting with Peter for a while about what we were going to watch that night, made a good sandwich for lunch, continued writing but felt the coffee wearing off and eventually worked on other tasks and went for walks in the snow. During the evening, I had spaghetti dinner with my family and watched the first four episodes of The Mandalorian with Peter. Overall, I'd say today was great! The writing portions of the day were fantastic, although I did feel periodic anxiety about Cameron later in the day - I've been feeling a mix of jealousy and fear over the idea that she has a boyfriend she hasn't told me about, but these worries are unfounded as far as I can tell. It was nice having it snow all day and even nicer watching it as I worked on writing for the first in a long time!

I offered to do a call (partially because I wanted to see her anyway), and I was happy to have made her feel better. Overall, I'd say today was a good day - I wasn't feeling super cheerful for most of it on account of my sleepiness, but seeing Cameron made me feel happy. Seeing her also cleared up my worries mentioned yesterday.
